---
import '../styles/components/feature-grid.css';
---

<div class="features-grid">
  <div class="feat">
    <div class="feat-k">核</div>
    <div class="feat-label">Hardware</div>
    <h3>GPU-accelerated <em>hardburn</em></h3>
    <p>
      Uses your NVIDIA NVENC, Intel QSV, or AMD AMF to burn subs at 6–12× real-time. CPU
      libx264 is the always-available fallback so machines without a supported GPU still ship.
    </p>
    <span class="feat-tag"><span class="ok">●</span> NVENC · QSV · AMF · libx264</span>
  </div>

  <div class="feat">
    <div class="feat-k">設</div>
    <div class="feat-label">Preset</div>
    <h3>One knob. <em>Zero</em> knob-turning.</h3>
    <p>
      The Balanced preset picks the encoder preset, CQ, and tune that match your hardware. Fast
      and Pristine variants land in v0.2 — for v0.1 there's one good default and no fiddle bar.
    </p>
    <span class="feat-tag">均 · balanced · sensible defaults</span>
  </div>

  <div class="feat">
    <div class="feat-k">単</div>
    <div class="feat-label">Single-file</div>
    <h3>One MKV. <em>One ASS.</em> Done.</h3>
    <p>
      Drop a video, drop the subtitle file, hit go. Live progress with fps, speed, bitrate, and
      ETA. Folder queue + cour batching land in v0.3 — v0.1 is the sharp single-file edition.
    </p>
    <span class="feat-tag">ass · ssa · srt · libass</span>
  </div>

  <div class="feat">
    <div class="feat-k">録</div>
    <div class="feat-label">Transparency</div>
    <h3>Full ffmpeg <em>stderr.</em></h3>
    <p>
      No black boxes. Every frame, every warning, every bitrate line is right there in the side
      panel. The bundled ffmpeg is the upstream BtbN build, unmodified — pinned by SHA-256.
    </p>
    <span class="feat-tag">ffmpeg 8.1 · sha-256 pinned</span>
  </div>

  <div class="feat" id="privacy">
    <div class="feat-k">夜</div>
    <div class="feat-label">Quiet</div>
    <h3>No cloud. <em>No account.</em></h3>
    <p>
      No sign-in, no telemetry, no analytics. ffmpeg fetches once at install, then never again.
      Auto-update checks are off by default — flip the toggle in Settings if you want them.
    </p>
    <span class="feat-tag"><span class="ok">●</span> 0 telemetry · auto-update opt-in</span>
  </div>

  <div class="feat">
    <div class="feat-k">無</div>
    <div class="feat-label">Free</div>
    <h3>Free. <em>Source-available.</em></h3>
    <p>
      Read it, audit it, file issues — see the LICENSE for redistribution terms. No pro tier,
      no "upgrade to unlock", no paid codecs. Pay with a star on GitHub if you feel like it.
    </p>
    <span class="feat-tag">source available · github.com/Shironex/moekoder</span>
  </div>
</div>
